Greetings Hanley Families! Our staff continues to work hard to get everything prepared for the upcoming school year! We're doing our best to ensure that this virtual experience is a successful one. Here are some things that you can expect moving forward.

* Class Lists will be Posted on DOJO Monday 8/31/20
* You will be able to pick up your students' supplies, technology and virtual learning schedule on Wednesday (9/2/20) and Thursday (9/3/20) from 9am-12pm
* Be on the lookout for your students' Classroom Dojo Invite

We're gearing up for year full of robust virtual Learning!

We can do this!!!

-Mrs. Stone

post_text: Today at 11:30 AM!
shared_text:
The Romine Group
May 13 at 11:05 AM ¬∑

Today's the day - happy Virtual Charter Day 2020! We're going LIVE on Facebook at 11:30AM, and we can't wait for you to join us! Follow these quick instructions to tune in and share our live post with YOUR friends, school Facebook page audience, etc.

Visit our MI Charters Facebook page around 11:30AM, when we'll go LIVE for the big program. We'll wait for about 5 minutes before getting started so everyone can tune in.

Once you find the video on our page, click the "Share" option. Either select "Share Now (Friends)" or to share to your school's Facebook page select "More Options" then "Share to a Page" and select your school's page.
Be sure to have your school swag on, and be ready to post a photo showing it off, along with a message about why you LOVE your charter school, in the comments!

https://www.facebook.com/MICharters/

Great News Hanley Families!

We are going to resume FREE food distribution this Monday 4/27/20! Meals will be available two days each week. Pick up times are Monday and Wednesday from 10am-12pm. Multiple meals will be prepared to ensure you have food between pick up days. Please remember that we are observing strict social distancing guidelines. Masks are strongly encouraged.

For everyone's safety:
- you must remain 6 feet apart from everyone
- please come into the foyer, get your meals and exit
immediately
- staff will be maintaining a safe distance and wearing appropriate protection please respect their distance

We are glad that we can continue to support our families during this time.

Great things are happening at Hanley!
Mrs. Stone

post_text:
Greetings Hanley Families! We have been busy preparing Learning Kits to support your student‚Äôs growth during this time. These kits are full of workbooks, manipulatives, games and so many other tools to make learning fun and accessible. There is one kit for each student (grades PreK-8). Your student‚Äôs teacher will be in contact with you regarding how to use your kits.

Distribution will take place this Monday April 20th in shifts. We will allow one person in the building at a time to pick up the kits. We will practice strict social distancing protocol for everyone‚Äôs safety. Tables are labeled for a quick grab and go.

Pick up times:
PreK-2nd grade: 8am-10am
3rd-5th grade: 10am-12pm
Middle School: 12pm-2pm

Thanks for all of your continued patience as we work through this process as a Hanley Team! You are all doing a wonderful job!

-Mrs. Stone

February 20 at 12:21 PM ¬∑

‚ñ∂Ô∏èWe Still Need Your Support! If you haven‚Äôt taken a moment to email our Governor, please do so today‚ùóÔ∏è

Governor Gretchen Whitmer presented her proposal for next year‚Äôs K-12 School Aid Budget.

‚úÖCharter students (and all others funded at the state minimum) are slated to receive a $225 per-pupil increase. Also included in the budget is extra funding for things like poverty/trauma & special education.

‚ùå Some budget items COMPLETELY EXCLUDE charter schools or fund them less.

Charter students = public school students.
Charter educators = public school teachers.
Charter families = public school families.

Every dollar counts, and we need equitable resources. Help us speak up to key decision-makers today!

üëâ bit.ly/2020mischoolaid

Please Take A Moment To Vote!

Just a few short months ago, Governor Whitmer vetoed $35M slated for charter students, using our kids as political leverage to achieve other budget goals. Together, we spoke up - 15,000+ teachers, parents, grandparents, school leaders and advocates alike - and our elected officials heard us loud and clear, restoring the funding after three long months.

Now, those same lawmakers are hard at work negotiating next year‚Äôs state budget, and they need to know that our students are a PRIORITY. Simply put, they need to hear that we won't settle for anything less than EQUALITY in this budget.

It only takes 60 seconds to send your local elected officials a message - YOUR voice has the potential for HUGE impact!

Born in Atlanta, Georgia, King is best known for advancing civil rights through nonviolence and civil disobedience, inspired by his Christian beliefs and the nonviolent activism of Mahatma Gandhi.

About the MI Charter AwardsüèÜ

Every year, the Charter School Awards give us a platform to highlight outstanding educators in Michigan's charter schools.

We rely entirely on anonymous nominations from parents, fellow teachers, school leaders and community members to shed light on those who are going above and beyond. Thanks to the generous support from General Agency Company & EMC Insurance Companies, the top five
Teacher of the Year and Admin of the Year finalists will each receive a $500 cash prize, and each will earn a platform to share their best practices throughout the year.

post_text: How You Can Help!
shared_text:
CHARTERSCHOOLS.ORG
Pawn Challenge

The Romine Group
October 29, 2019 at 12:07 PM ¬∑

#PawnChallenge

On Oct. 1, 2019, Governor Gretchen Whitmer vetoed a $240 per-pupil funding increase for charter school students, while OK'ing funding for other public school students - all in an effort to bargain for road funding. The #PawnChallenge calls on charter educators, advocates, parents and students to share real stories, about our real kids - showing Gov. Whitmer & our elected officials that MI charter students are not just faceless pawns to be used as bargaining chips in their political game. You Can Help

October 17, 2019 at 12:19 PM ¬∑

Please Make Your Voice Heard:

No matter what side of the aisle you stand on, I challenge you to ask more of your elected officials and Governor Whitmer. Ask them to hear your story. Ask them why our charter students have been targeted with this funding cut. Let them know that we are NOT collateral damage, not a sacred cow, not a hostage - today, or ever.

We are the voices of Michigan's charter schools, and we demand to be heard.

Follow The Link - Tell the Governor and your lawmakers that your funding isn‚Äôt up for grabs - today, or any other day.
